# Block attachment registration checklist

When adding a new block-level NSTextAttachment subclass, it MUST be added to these guards in TodoEditorRepresentable.swift:

1. `styleTodoParagraphs()` -- the `isImageParagraph` attachment type check
2. `shouldChangeText` -- the `hasBlockAttachment` type check

**Why:** `styleTodoParagraphs()` runs on every text change and applies `baseParagraphStyle()` (with `maximumLineHeight ~20pt`) to unrecognized paragraphs. This hard ceiling prevents the layout manager from using the attachment cell's actual height, causing the overlay to overlap surrounding content. This was the ROOT CAUSE of the file extract preview height bug (2026-04-02) -- `NoteFileAttachment` with viewMode != .tag was missing from the block attachment detection, so extracted previews were treated as body text paragraphs. It took 6+ failed fix attempts across 2 sessions before this was identified.

**How to apply:** Any time a new `NSTextAttachment` subclass is created for a block embed, grep for the existing attachment type lists (`NoteImageAttachment`, `NoteCalloutAttachment`, `NoteCodeBlockAttachment`, `NoteTabsAttachment`, `NoteCardSectionAttachment`, `NoteFileAttachment`) and add the new type to every list. For `NoteFileAttachment`, the check is conditional: `(attachment is NoteFileAttachment && (attachment as! NoteFileAttachment).viewMode != .tag)` because tag-mode file attachments are inline, not block-level.

## Current block attachment types (as of 2026-04-02)

- `NoteImageAttachment`
- `NoteCalloutAttachment`
- `NoteCodeBlockAttachment`
- `NoteTabsAttachment`
- `NoteCardSectionAttachment`
- `NoteFileAttachment` (viewMode != .tag only)
